Yunju Temple is located in Xi'an, Shaanxi Province. It is a Buddhist nunnery. It was founded during the Tang Dynasty (618 - 907), and renovated at the end of the Ming Dynasties (1368 - 1644). It was said that the Emperor Li Shimin had it built for his mother to worship everyday.

Jiaohe Ruins in Turpan, Xinjiang Autonomous Region. It was built with rammed earth and bricks 2,300 years ago, controlled by the residents of Gaochang. Taken by the Uighars, it was eventually abandoned during the Yuan Dynasty (1271 -1368), perhaps due to dwindling water supplies.
